The paper deals with statistical shape models and their application to medical image analysis, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also proposes a new framework for dynamic multi-object statistical modelling, which involves optimization and prediction, making it relevant to artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also deals with the analysis of human joints, which is a topic in graphics (cs.GR) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
